Hello Everyone 💖 
Pasta e piselli with ricotta, or pasta and peas, is a simple Italian pasta dish that's easy to make with just a few ingredients.  The creamy pasta and the sweet peas marry together beautifully with ricotta cheese for the ultimate comfort food.
✅️ Ingrediences✅️
✅️ shell pasta
✅️ Ricotta
✅️ peas
✅️ Olive oil
✅️ garlic
✅️ onion
✅️ pasta water
✅️ grated parmesan 
Start by sauting in two tablespoons of extra virgin olive oil. One tablespoon of minced garlic and two tablespoons of minced onion. Until translucent and just beginning to brown. Add the juice from one lemon. Meanwhile, cook your pasta el dante. Add one ladle of pasta water to your saute pan. Add either one cup of white wine or vegetable stock. simmer  for 10 minutes, then add three cups of peas simmer until peas are cooked through about five minutes. Take it off the fire and add two cups of ricotta cheese. Toss your pasta in this delicious sauce, adjust your seasonings, and enjoy. Rösti is a potato dish, where grated potatoes are fried in a pan. Unlike American hash browns, which are loosely sautéed, with Rösti, the grated potatoes are compressed into a “pancake,” which is crisped on each side Unlike latkes, there is no egg or flour to bind the potatoes. 
 This potato  pancake originated in Switzerland  because of its close proximity to Italy rösti made its way to italian tables.
The options are endless for adding ingredients to the crisp  potatoes, however I’ve found that simplicity often works the best in creating a deliciously flavorful side. I topped it simply with sour cream and dill.

✅️ potatoes

Cantucci are perhaps the best known of Italian cookies. Simple to make, easily customizable with your favorite flavor combination, and perfect for holiday gifts and cookie trays!
The word biscotti literally means twice (bis) cooked (cotto) and, in fact, cantucci, are the emblem of twice-baked cookies. They are extremely simple to make. You just have to mix all the ingredients together, shape the dough into long logs and bake them. Then, when the logs are still warm, cut them into slices and cook them again.
✅️ Ingredients ✅️
✅️ 3 eggs 
✅️ 11/2 cups sugar
✅️ 2 1/2 cups flour
✅️ 2 teaspoon baking powder 
✅️ 3 cups almonds 
✅️ 1 tablespoon orange zest 
✅️ 1 tablespoons vanilla 
✅️Instructions ✅️
Preheat the oven to  375-degree 
In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, and baking powder.
Roughly chop half of the almonds.
In a large bowl, combine sugar and eggs. Whisk for a couple of minutes until the compound turns lighter in color.
Add flour, baking powder, orange zest and  vanilla. Mix everything together until well combined.
When you achieve a crumbly texture, add the almonds, both chopped and whole.
Shape the dough into three long logs (about 1 1/2 inches high) and place them on your baking sheet, lined with parchment paper. 
brush the log’s surface with egg.
Bake for 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Take the logs out of the oven and lower the temperature to 300 degrees. 
Cut the logs diagonally into 1/2-inch slices using a serrated knife.
Put the slices back onto the baking tray, bake for another 8 to 10 minutes. ENJOY ⚘️
